    "source": "director",
    "movements": [
      {
        "turn": 1,
        "name": "Act 1",
        "intent": "[The hearing room settles into its first silence, damp coats steaming by the wall and the wreck's question hanging before anyone has named it. Outside, the weather presses at the windows like a second jury.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 5,
        "name": "Act 2",
        "intent": "[The sealed bundle gives way to a different stillness, not the heat of accusation but the colder air that follows when a room must watch its own certainty tested. The lamps are trimmed lower, the clerk clears a bare space at the table, and the next act enters under glass, wax, and official hands.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 9,
        "name": "Act 3",
        "intent": "[The room lets the dismissed accusation fall without ceremony, and the silence after it has a harder edge than anger. A darker business waits beyond the cleared table now: not blame by habit, but traces, handling, and the cost of proving that a dead place was made to speak.]"
      }
    ],
    "tutorNotes": []
  },
